<1ST_LINE>r a PM-APAppointment     08-23 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AP Appointment,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pyle Named ACOB In Dallas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   David Pyle, Associated Press correspondent in
Providence, R.I., for five years and most recently the AP's news
editor in Dallas, has been named assistant chief of bureau in
Dallas.
   Sue Cross, the news cooperative's Juneau, Alaska, correspondent,
will replace Pyle as news editor.
   The appointments were announced Monday by Dallas Chief of Bureau
John Lumpkin.
   Pyle, 34, joined the AP in Omaha, Neb., in 1979 and became news
editor there in 1981. He was named correspondent in charge of the
AP's Providence bureau in 1983 and became Dallas news editor last
month.
   Pyle is a native of Des Moines, Iowa, and a graduate of the
University of Iowa.
   Ms. Cross joined the AP in Cincinnati in 1983. She transferred
to Columbus later that year and in 1984 was named correspondent in
Toledo. She has been Juneau correspondent since 1986.
   Ms. Cross is a native of Cleveland and a graduate of Ohio State
University.
</TEXT>
