<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--China-Holdup     08-23 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-Holdup,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Peasant Captured, Another Blows Himself Up After Botched
Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two peasants wielding a home-made pistol and a
dagger killed two clerks in robbing a bank in south China, but one
was captured and the other blew himself up when surrounded by
soldiers, a newspaper reported today.
   The official People's Daily (Renmin Ribao) said the two robbers,
from the outskirts of the provincial capital of Kunming, held up
the Industrial and Commercial Bank in Wenshan county at noon on
Aug. 17.
   It said the two killed two clerks and made off with $9,000 but a
third clerk, injured in the attack, sounded an alarm.
   Seven soldiers and other citizens gave chase, and one of the
robbers set off an explosive and killed himself when cornered. The
other was captured.
   Wenshan is in a heavily militarized area near China's tense
border with Vietnam.
</TEXT>
