<HEAD>At Least 25 Injured In Restaurant Explosion</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout, with 25 injured, other details. No
pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion shattered a
fast-food restaurant today in the coastal city of East London,
injuring at least 25 people, police said.
   Major Trevor Hayes, a police spokesman, said no one was killed.
He said the cause of the blast was not known.
   The explosion occurred about 1:15 p.m. at a Wimpy hamburger
restaurant in East London's central business area.
   Witneses said they heard screams from the restaurant and saw
injured people being taken away by rescue workers. Hayes said he
did not know how many of the victims were seriously hurt.
   Police have blamed the outlawed African National Congress for a
recent series of bombings in civilian areas. The ANC said last week
that some civilian targets had been attacked by guerrillas acting
against their leaders' instructions.
   The ANC is the main guerrilla group fighting to overthrown the
South African government and end apartheid.
