<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Initiations     08-23 0271</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Initiations,0279</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boulder High Initiation Turns Ugly, Witnesses Say</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOULDER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An initiation for incoming Boulder High
School sophomore girls allegedly involved girls smearing themselves
with chicken excrement and torturing chickens to death, a newspaper
reported today.
   Up to 10 chickens may have been killed or injured, according to
accounts given to The Boulder Daily Camera by students and other
witnesses who were at the mall Sunday evening.
   However, police did not report any evidence of such activity.
Hal Nees, division chief of patrol, said three officers were sent
and apparently did not find that chickens were being killed because
they took no enforcement action.
   Initiating sophomores is a longstanding tradition in Boulder.
   Some initiators threw chickens high into the air to fall on
sophomores who were grouped in a circle, or onto the pavement, the
newspaper said.
   One sophomore, who asked that her name not be used, told the
newspaper that initiators took her group of six girls to a park and
forced them to smear fresh chicken excrement on each other. In
addition, the initiators made the girls kiss a beef tongue which
was dripping blood, she said.
   Boulder High School principal Marcy McMillan called on Monday
for an investigation by police and the Boulder County Humane
Society. ``We are strongly opposed to any kind of initiation,'' she
said.
   Sally Shelton of Atlanta, visiting for her son's University of
Colorado freshman orientation, said she saw 10 girls doing
cartwheels while holding chickens by the neck.
   ``Those girls looked frightened, and they looked like they were
in a sort of a stupor,'' she said.
</TEXT>
