<HEAD>Homeless Man Bleeds to Death From Cuts on Razor-Rimmed Fence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homeless man apparently bled to death early
Tuesday after he slashed his arms trying to scale a fence rimmed
with razor wire, the Transit Authority reported.
   The man was found in the TA's material storage yard in Brooklyn,
according to TA spokesman Albert O'Leary. The man, in his late 30s,
had been dead for several hours.
   O'Leary said he had no knowledge of how the man got into the
rail yard, which is encircled by a double set of chain-link fences
each topped with razor wire.
   ``Apparently the man had been inside the yard and tried to get
out by climbing over the fence,'' O'Leary said. ``He cut both of
his arms and his wrists on the top of the fence. He then climbed or
fell off the fence and walked a couple of hundred feet where he sat
down by a pile of railroad ties and apparently bled to death.''
   The man carried no identifying papers and was apparently
homeless, O'Leary said.
