<HEAD>Fruit, Nut Exports Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Exports of U.S. horticultural products such as
fruit and nuts totaled $246 million in June, a 20 percent increase
from a year earlier, the Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   The shipments, not counting those to Canada, including a strong
showing by all products within the horticultural category.
   ``Sales of fresh fruit and tree nuts accounted for 49 percent of
export value in June,'' the department's Foreign Agricultural
Service reported. ``Inshell almond exports reached $21.7 million,
with most shipments going to the European Community and Japan.''
   Japan also accounted for 86 percent of the $21.6 million worth
of lemons and grapefruit exported in June, the report said.
