<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cranberries,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cranberries Hit Sweet Number</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This year's cranberry crop is forecast at a
record 3.73 million barrels, up 12 percent from the 1987 harvest of
3.32 million barrels, the Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   Massachusetts, the leading producer, is expected to harvest
almost 1.83 million barrels, up 26 percent from last year, said the
department's Agricultural Statistics Board.
   The New Jersey crop was forecast at 310,000 barrels, up 11
percent from 1987; Oregon, 150,000 barrels; up 6 percent;
Washington, 108,000 barrels, down 17 percent; and Wisconsin, 1.34
million barrels, up 1 percent.
   A barrel is 100 pounds of cranberries.
