<DOCNO> AP880823-0151 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-23-88 1922EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-SAfrica-Explosion     08-23 0310</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-SAfrica-Explosion,0319</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Limpet Mine Shatters Restaurant at Lunch, 23 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A limpet mine clamped under a
table at a restaurant in the coastal city of East London exploded
Tuesday, injuring at least 23 people, police said.
   About 10 people were inside the Wimpy restaurant across from
city hall in East London's central business district when the blast
occurred at 1:15 p.m. The injured included diners and passersby,
authorities said.
   Three women were seriously injured from shrapnel wounds and
burns and were hospitalized. The rest, half of them black and the
rest white, were treated for cuts and shock and released, hospital
officials said.
   Maj. Trevor Hayes, spokesman for the East London area police,
said a limpet mine believed to have been planted by the outlawed
African National Congress was attached underneath a table next to a
window facing the street.
   A deep hole was blasted in the floor, tables were ripped out and
the kitchen and interior were destroyed by fire.
   Ference Makovinir, 35, said he was blown through the window by
the blast as he and his wife, Theonie, 28, were having coffee.
   ``I don't know what happened,'' he said. ``I heard this
thunderous noise and saw the flames and the next thing I was thrown
out of the window. I went back into the place to look for my
wife,'' who he said was in shock but unhurt.
   Two other Wimpy restaurants in South Africa have been bombed
since June 1986, and the company announced it would now discuss
increasing its security.
   Police have blamed the ANC for a series of recent bombings in
civilian areas. The ANC said last week that some civilian targets
had been attacked by guerrillas acting against their leaders'
instructions.
   The ANC is the main guerrilla group fighting to overthrow the
South African government and end apartheid.
</TEXT>
