<1ST_LINE>r i AM-LynchMob     08-23 0272</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Lynch Mob,0279</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Brazilian Lynch Mob Goes on Rampage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One person was killed and dozens were
hurt in a battle between members of a mob and police who kept them
from lynching two men suspected of raping and murdering a teen-age
girl, authorities said Tuesday.
   The violence took place Monday in the city of Araraquara in
southeastern Brazil, 170 miles northwest of Sao Paulo.
   Capt. Nicolau Lambort of Araraquara state police said the
grandfather of the 14-year-old girl was shot to death in the
four-hour melee. Lambort said by telephone police did not know who
fired the shot.
   He said 14 policemen and 30-40 townspeople were injured, two
with gunshot wounds in their legs. No one was arrested.
   Lambort said a mob of 800 to 1,000 men and women tried to lynch
two men ``accused of the kidnap, rape and stabbing death of a
14-year-old girl abducted last Friday as she was walking home from
school.''
   He said the mob was ``doubly enraged'' because on Sunday, one
day after the girl was buried, ``unidentified individuals unearthed
her body and sexually molested it.'
   The captain said police quickly removed the two suspects and
took them to another city when the infuriated mob gathered in front
of the police station.
   ``Frustrated in their lynching attempt, the mob started hurling
rocks at the police station. Then they went on a rampage, smashing
windows of three banks and damaging other buildings in the city,''
he reported.
   He said Araraquara's 230-member police force was unable to quell
the riot and 200 more police officers were called in from four
neighboring cities.
</TEXT>
