<2ND_LINE>PM-Dairy Sale,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Weeks Dairy Sold To Crowley Foods</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Weeks Dairy Foods, Inc. of Concord, the
state's leading processor and distributor of fresh milk products
and ice creams, has reached an agreement to be acquired by Crowley
Foods Inc. of Binghamton, N.Y.
   The sale is subject to approval by shareholders of both
companies, John F. Weeks Jr., president of Weeks Dairy, announced
Monday.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
   Weeks, founded in Laconia in 1930, distributes products to
retail grocery stores, supermarkets and food service establishments
throughout New Hampshire, Maine, Vermont and Massachusetts.
   Crowley, a subsidiary of Wessanen U.S.A., manufactures a variety
of dairy and food products for distribution in 22 states.
   Weeks said his company's processing and distribution facilities
will continue to operate without any management or employee
changes. Weeks has 275 employees at its administrative offices,
processing plant and main distribution facilities in Concord and
distribution centers in Chesterfield, N.H., and Abington, Mass.
   Weeks said the acquisition will enable Weeks to continue as one
of New England's largest dairy firms.
</TEXT>
