<1ST_LINE>r f AM-DesignAwards     08-23 0364</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Design Awards,0386</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gas Station, Tractor, Printer and Cars Among Design Winners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Amoco gas station, a Case IH tractor, a Qume
printer and cars from Oldsmobile and Lamborghini are among the
products to be honored Wednesday as winners of industrial design
awards.
   Twelve designs out of 310 entries will receive the 1988
Industrial Design Excellence Award (IDEA) from the Industrial
Designers Society of America at ceremonies in New York.
   The designs are based on innovation, use of appropriate
materials, efficient production methods, benefits to the user and
client, and the appeal of the appearance.
   ``This year's IDEA winners underscore the fact that good design
is good business,'' Charles W. Pelly, the jury chairman, said in a
prepared statement.
   By the rules, all the products are on the market except those in
the categories of design explorations and student design projects.
   The designers society estimates more than $1 billion is spent
annually on industrial design services in the United States.
   Awards were given in 12 of the 13 eligible categories. No winner
was picked in the category of signs because there were fewer than
10 entries.
   Here are the winning entries, along with the clients for whom
the designs were done:
   _Products: Spacemaker Plus, an under-the-cabinet unit containing
a coffeemaker, can opener, knife sharpener and light, for Black &
Decker Corp.
   _Toys and Games: Voyager, a toy headset that plays music or
story cartridges, for Texas Instruments Inc.
   _3-D Packaging: Aqua Color Box, for holding dry water colors,
for Herlitz GmbH of West Germany.
   _Transportation: 1988 Oldsmobile Cutlass Supreme, for General
Motors Corp.
   _Equipment: Qume Sigma Non-Impact Printer, for Qume Corp.
   _Instruments: Ciba Corning Diagnostics 550 Express Chemistry
Analyzer, for Ciba Corning Diagnostics.
   _Machinery: Case IH 7100 Magnum Tractor, for J.I. Case Co.
   _Design Explorations: Lamborghini Portofino, a show car, for
Chrysler Corp.
   _Furniture and Fixtures: Newhouse Group Furniture, for Herman
Miller Inc.
   _Exhibits: Metropolitan Funiture Westweek 1987 Exhibition, a
temporary exhibit, for Metropolitan Furniture Corp.
   _Environments: Amoco Station of the Future, for Amoco Oil Co.
   _Student Design Projects: Compuchart, a computer terminal for
use in hospitals, designed by Ron Boeder while at San Jose State
University. (No client.)
</TEXT>
