<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market drifted lazily lower today,
with blue-chip issues outperforming the broader market.
   Market analysts said a pair of new economic reports showing a
rise in consumer prices in July and a decline in durable goods
orders had been largely anticipated, and failed to provide traders
with much direction.
   That left stock traders with many of the same concerns about
interest rates and the economy that have weighed on the market for
weeks.
