   The reports sparked a mild rally in the bond market, where
traders have been wary of signs of accelerating inflation combined
with economic strength.
   But stocks failed to muster as much enthusiasm as bonds did.
   ``The reports were in line with expectations, but it's not a
strong market. There are still a lot of remnants of selling
pressure. We are not out of the woods yet,'' said Charles Jensen, a
market analyst for MKI Securities Corp. in New York.
