<2ND_LINE>BC-Steel Prices, 1st Ld-Writethru,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>USX Raises Tin Mill Prices 9.5 Percent</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New 4th graf on Alcoa statement, picks up 4th graf pvs, USX,
the...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USX Corp. announced a 9.5 percent increase in
tin mill prices Tuesday, effective Oct. 1.
   Tin-coated steel sheet is the prime packaging material for
canned food.
   The increase comes at a time when high prices for aluminum
sheet, the prime packaging material for canned soft drinks and
beer, have prompted beverage makers to consider steel packaging.
   Aluminum Co. of America, the nation's largest aluminum producer,
said it would maintain current prices through Dec. 31 on aluminum
used in beverage can bodies, ends and tabs.
   USX, the nation's largest steelmaker and historical price
leader, revealed the price move in announcing plans to invest $41
million to improve tin operations at its Gary Works near Chicago.
   Work has begun on equipment to more uniformly coat the steel
with tin and to improve the mill production capacity.
</TEXT>
