<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     08-23 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 0.9 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.838 million tons in
the week ended Aug. 20, an increase of 0.9 percent from the
previous week's 1.822 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 86.2 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 85.4 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
64.097 million net tons, an increase of 19.3 percent from the
53.742 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.9 percent of capacity,
compared with 75.4 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Aug. 20: Northeast
Coast, 262,000; Pittsburgh, 195,000; Youngstown, 91,000; Lake Erie,
153,000; Detroit, 160,000; Chicago, 499,000; Midwest, 182,000;
Southern, 207,000; and Western, 89,000.
</TEXT>
